[metadata]
Name:Torch the Tower deals base 2 damage (unbargained)
Goal:Win
Turns:3
Difficulty:Easy
Description:Torch the Tower (SVar:X:Count$Bargain.3.2) deals 2 damage to target creature or planeswalker when cast without paying the optional Bargain cost (no artifact/enchantment/token to sacrifice). Before the fix (mtg-863), Count$Bargain.3.2 fell through to Fixed(0) and the spell dealt 0 damage. After the fix, CountExpression::Bargain evaluates conservatively to the unbargained_value (2), so a 2/2 Grizzly Bears takes lethal damage and dies. P0 controls 2 Mountains (mana for {R}) and holds Torch the Tower; P1 controls a Grizzly Bears (2/2). No artifacts/enchantments/tokens in play, so Bargain cannot be paid — the spell should deal exactly 2.

